      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness compared against experimental measurements from two independent laboratories. Mean absolute percentage error 4.2%; E/uval = 1.31 < 1.96. Acceptance criterion satisfied. A comprehensive UQ campaign was conducted prior to finalisation, including Latin hypercube sampling across material property and geometric tolerance distributions (n=500 runs), confirming that first-order sensitivity indices for cortical bone modulus and screw-rod interface friction coefficient account for 78% of output variance. These UQ activities informed parameter bounding and acceptance threshold setting for the validation comparison.",
